    "feat": {
        "name": "Exaltation Overwhelming",
        "type": "stat_block_section",
        "subtype": "feat",
        "text": "Raising your weapon or fist aloft, you begin to gleam with dazzling radiance. You fulminate with power and glory, making it clear to all who see you that your legend is real and possibly even greater than purported. Spend a Mythic Point. All enemies who can see you must succeed at a Will saving throw against your class DC or become frightened 3 (frightened 4 on a critical failure). You and any ally who can see you may choose to Strike or Stride as a free action. Any of these Strikes are made at mythic proficiency.",
        "level": 18,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Emotion",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 60,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 455",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 455,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "fb5f8b3d849b073e1514a6a025810470",
                "text": "This effect alters a creature\u2019s emotions. Effects with this trait always have the mental trait as well. Creatures with special training or that have mechanical or artificial intelligence are immune to emotion effects."
            },
            {
                "name": "Fear",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 68,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 456",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 456",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 456,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "9a5cea6bfb849deb16206c68f8d113a5",
                "text": "Fear effects evoke the emotion of fear. Effects with this trait always have the mental and emotion traits as well."
            },
            {
                "name": "Mental",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 106,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 458,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "6a1f80610baa3617c1597f49c6406313",
                "text": "A mental effect can alter the target\u2019s mind. It has no effect on an object or a mindless creature."
            },
            {
                "name": "Mythic",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "War of Immortals",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                            "alt": "War of Immortals pg. 69",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 232
                        },
                        "page": 69
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "40b5d9c5e49dbe2aea5d7ecf38d950f3",
                "text": "Options with this trait grant or utilize mythic power. Feats with the mythic trait can only be taken by mythic characters, who are typically characters with a mythic Calling.  \n  \n Monsters with the mythic trait have access to a pool of Mythic Points and are particularly strong for creatures of their level. Many mythic monsters are either resistant or entirely immune to attacks from non-mythic creatures and weapons.  \n  \n Spells with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to be cast, and items with the mythic trait require the expenditure of a Mythic Point in order to use their activated abilities.  \n  \n Weapons with the mythic trait overcome the resistances and immunities of mythic monsters."
            },
            {
                "name": "Visual",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 163,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 463",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 463,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "abcdb0d656f37cebdbee9dca267ef899",
                "text": "A visual effect can affect only creatures that can see it. This applies only to visible parts of the effect, as determined by the GM."
            }
        ],
